	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=18657&mid=106513477443687>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=18657&mid=106513477443687>An essential bard item</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=18657&mid=106513477443687#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Oct 2nd 6:59 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=223853><span id=Scholar>RabbiSatan</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>29 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>As Master omnistriker said, the VoTS doesn't increase your singing skill by adding 6 points to 235, rather, it adds 0.6 to your overall singing modifier.<br><br>The drop rate of the VoTS is somewhat random, it can vary from 2 drops out of 3 disciples, to hell camps of 20 disciples. From what I've read, the average amount of time it takes to camp the VoTS is around several hours, roughly 9, and drops once out of roughly 9 to 10 disciples.<br><br>Disciple Yelwinz himself is not that difficult, I have read of bards that were able to solo him, but however, I did my usual tactic of SoS / Mez.<br><br>The tricky part to Disciple Yelwinz is the actual pulling of him. As like most snakes in the temple, if you don't properly guide him through, he will get stuck on the ledge above the sliding doors. Which gets tiresome when pulling his caster PHs.<br><br>What I did was lull the other snakes (Gets tougher with the 2nd Rzoth), play HoS, then snare. And once the snake / Disciple Yelwinz was out of the first door, I would mez drag them through the second door, and from that area there, continue with SoS / Mez.<br><br>There are 2 options in which to reach Disciple Yelwinz and his PHs:<br><br>1) Have a rogue friend / bot with maximum picklock skill pick through the door to reach the camp. This may become a bit tiresome with your friend, but if you have a bot, this is the easier way.<br><br>2) Got this information from my fellow bards at the Concert Hall boards, and decided to share it here:<br><br>(You will NEED invisibility and some form of levitation, if you don't have some form of clicky levitation like singing steel boots, you could try to lull the snakes and play Aria, and follow the steps below)<br><br>Once comming into the basement via the water tube, turn left or right, onto the thin blue, slanted ledge surrounding the tube and the snakes. Travel to the back of the ledge, and run into the tube, and look up at 45 degrees with varying deviations to see which angle is the best to make you walk up. Some models / races work better than the others at travelling up the tube, but from experience and information at the Concert Hall, Halfling form is the best.<br><br>After you've walked high enough, simply fly over to the back wall, and follow the wall over to the campsite area.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Sat Feb 14 12:09:55 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
